Download and parse the SEC's recent filings feed, and XBRL filings feed:

{% raw %}

secMostRecentListUrl[source]

secMostRecentListUrl(count=100)

Returns the URL for the SEC's atom-format feed of most recent filings.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

printXmlParseWarning[source]

printXmlParseWarning(msg, el)

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

getRecentChunk[source]

getRecentChunk(count=100)

Parses the SEC's atom-format feed of most recent filings and returns a list of tuples: [(fileDate, cikName, accNo, formType, cik), ... ] with the most recent filings first

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

getXbrlFeed[source]

getXbrlFeed()

Test downloading and parsing the SEC's recent filings feed and XBRL filings feed:

{% raw %} 
l = getRecentChunk()
print('recent filings feed:')
utils.printSamp(l,5)
assert len(l)==100, 'parsing SEC recent filings feed'
print()

lxbrl = getXbrlFeed()
print('XBRL filings feed:')
utils.printSamp(lxbrl,5)
assert len(lxbrl)==200, 'parsing SEC XBRL filings feed'
